Docker Volumes
A way to store data outside a container so it does NOT disappear when the container stops or is deleted. A folder in a physical host filesystem is mounted into the virtual file system of docker

Types
docker run
-v /home/mount/data:/var/lib/mysql/data
    Host directory       : Container directory/path

docker run
-v /var/lib/mysql/data
This does not specify host directory, docker does -anonymous volumes

docker run 
-v name: /var/lib/mysql/data
It specifies the name of the folder on the host file system - named volumes 
*you can mount the same volume name to two different folders.

LAYERS
Each Docker instruction is a layer of the image
